column37: Does not have an exciting pedigree but belied 40-1 odds when very respectable third of seven (4l behind Mossvale Diva) on recent debut at Catterick (5f, good), shaping very much as though today's longer trip might suit.

column37: 8,000gns foal; fourth foal; sister to 5f 2yo winner Jeany May (RPR 70), half-sister to 6f winner El Montejean (79); dam 5f winner (70); would be a very rare first-time-out winner for the stable.

column4: Virgin Bet Every Saturday Money Back EBF Restricted Novice Stakes (Bands B-D) (EBF Rest' Qual) (GBB)

column37: In the frame all seven starts (5f-6f), including five second-place finishes; gave it a good shot from the front at Catterick (5f, good) 16 days ago and has the ideal draw from which to attack here; big player.

column37: Seemed to better his low-key debut when second of five behind 1-14 favourite at Redcar (1m, good to firm) three weeks ago but that race was slowly run and the value of the form is questionable.

column37: 15-race maiden who showed some fair form for Andrew Balding but left that stable after a disappointing 7f run in June and has been safely held in two sprint handicaps for new yard; back up in trip here; needs to get career back on track.

column4: Xenon Workplace Handicap (GBBPlus Race)

column36: Back on track with front-running win at Sandown in July and now 4-6 in handicaps
column37: Suffered a couple of blips in June but bounced back with front-running win in refitted cheekpieces at Sandown (1m6f, good) in July and is now 4-6 since switched to handicaps this season; may yet have more to offer.

column4: Xenon Workplace Handicap (GBBPlus Race)
column20: 6/5 Gentle Warrior, 5/1 Scarlet Moon, 11/2 Navid, 8/1 Minhad,  John T, 12/1 Schemaya, 14/1 Triple Gee
column36: Safely held in two handicaps since winning three-runner maiden in June
column37: Won three-runner Salisbury maiden (1m4f, good to firm) in June, on third start, but was safely held in both subsequent handicaps (1m6f/2m); needs new cheekpieces to generate some improvement.

column4: Xenon Workplace Handicap (GBBPlus Race)
column20: 6/5 Gentle Warrior, 5/1 Scarlet Moon, 11/2 Navid, 8/1 Minhad,  John T, 12/1 Schemaya, 14/1 Triple Gee
column36: Both handicap runs (11.5f/1m2f) were very respectable and he's well worth a crack at 1m6f
column37: Yet to make any further progress since winning 1m4f Newbury novice in May but his first two handicap runs (11.5f/1m2f) were very respectable and he's worth a crack at today's longer trip; swaps visor for new blinkers.

column4: Xenon Workplace Handicap (GBBPlus Race)
column20: 6/5 Gentle Warrior, 5/1 Scarlet Moon, 11/2 Navid, 8/1 Minhad,  John T, 12/1 Schemaya, 14/1 Triple Gee
column36: Below form on AW debut but made solid start to handicap career on turf beforehand
column37: Scored on handicap debut at Windsor (11.4f, good to firm) in May and ran well in defeat on her next two outings (1m2f/1m4f); weak in the betting and well below form on last month's AW debut but has possibilities if back on song over new trip.

column4: Xenon Workplace Handicap (GBBPlus Race)
column20: 6/5 Gentle Warrior, 5/1 Scarlet Moon, 11/2 Navid, 8/1 Minhad,  John T, 12/1 Schemaya, 14/1 Triple Gee
column36: 0-5 but kept on well for second of four at Salisbury last time and may yet do better
column37: A maiden after five runs but rebounded from disappointing handicap debut with keeping-on second of four at Salisbury (1m4f, good to firm) in July and may yet have a bigger run in him; moves up in trip today.

column4: Xenon Workplace Handicap (GBBPlus Race)
column20: 6/5 Gentle Warrior, 5/1 Scarlet Moon, 11/2 Navid, 8/1 Minhad,  John T, 12/1 Schemaya, 14/1 Triple Gee
column36: Aided by cheekpieces lately, most notably when making all at Salisbury two runs ago
column37: Seemingly aided by cheekpieces on recent outings and got off the mark with front-running success at Salisbury (1m6f, good to firm; front pair well clear) in July, on ninth start; beaten at short odds over 2m since but still ran well, and remains one to be interested in.

column4: Xenon Workplace Handicap (GBBPlus Race)
column20: 6/5 Gentle Warrior, 5/1 Scarlet Moon, 11/2 Navid, 8/1 Minhad,  John T, 12/1 Schemaya, 14/1 Triple Gee
column27: Irish National Stud Mare Syndicate II
column32: Hambleton Racing Ltd XXXV & E Burke
column36: Escapes penalty for last week's clearcut Haydock win and is 7lb well in; obvious claims
column37: Has solid record in handicaps since last autumn and drew clear to win apprentice jockeys' race by over 3l at Haydock (1m6f, good) one week ago; escapes a penalty and is 7lb well in here; will be hard to beat if in similar form.

column4: Virgin Bet Supports Safe Gambling Handicap

column37: Long in the tooth now but ended last year with a Tapeta win and has held his own in some pretty competitive 7f turf handicaps this season; didn't fire last time but has possibilities from favourable draw.

column4: Virgin Bet Supports Safe Gambling Handicap
column20: 9/4 Mayday Malone, 13/2 Spirit Genie,  One More, 7/1 Documenting,  Benacre, 9/1 Zero Carbon, 10/1 Stratocracy, 14/1 Stanage, 20/1 Kindest Nation, 25/1 Maxi Boy,  Azure Zain,  He's A Gentleman
column36: C&D winner; not at best this season but ran quite well last week and remains well treated
column37: Three wins in 2024, including valuable C&D handicap; not in same form this season but was denied clear run when fourth at Ascot (1m, soft) a week ago and remains on a good mark; swaps visor for refitted cheekpieces.

column4: Virgin Bet Supports Safe Gambling Handicap
column20: 9/4 Mayday Malone, 13/2 Spirit Genie,  One More, 7/1 Documenting,  Benacre, 9/1 Zero Carbon, 10/1 Stratocracy, 14/1 Stanage, 20/1 Kindest Nation, 25/1 Maxi Boy,  Azure Zain,  He's A Gentleman
column36: Not beaten far at Glorious Goodwood last time but wide drawn dents appeal here
column37: Not beaten far in very competitive handicap at Glorious Goodwood (7f, good) in late July but is yet to make any significant further progress since winning seasonal debut in March and is poorly drawn here.

column4: Virgin Bet Supports Safe Gambling Handicap
column20: 9/4 Mayday Malone, 13/2 Spirit Genie,  One More, 7/1 Documenting,  Benacre, 9/1 Zero Carbon, 10/1 Stratocracy, 14/1 Stanage, 20/1 Kindest Nation, 25/1 Maxi Boy,  Azure Zain,  He's A Gentleman
column36: Progressive 3yo who has already won over C&D this summer and has the inside stall today
column37: Progressive 3yo who landed a good prize for Jay Mackay over C&D (good) in June and was also on target at Doncaster (7f, good to firm) last month; makes obvious appeal from the inside stall.

column4: Virgin Bet Supports Safe Gambling Handicap
column20: 9/4 Mayday Malone, 13/2 Spirit Genie,  One More, 7/1 Documenting,  Benacre, 9/1 Zero Carbon, 10/1 Stratocracy, 14/1 Stanage, 20/1 Kindest Nation, 25/1 Maxi Boy,  Azure Zain,  He's A Gentleman
column36: Absent since 6f AW second in May but well drawn for this stable debut; market may guide
column37: Much better known for his AW exploits but this return to turf should not be a problem; absent since finishing second at Kempton (6f) for Adrian Wintle in May but well drawn here; market may guide on stable debut.

column4: Virgin Bet Supports Safe Gambling Handicap
column20: 9/4 Mayday Malone, 13/2 Spirit Genie,  One More, 7/1 Documenting,  Benacre, 9/1 Zero Carbon, 10/1 Stratocracy, 14/1 Stanage, 20/1 Kindest Nation, 25/1 Maxi Boy,  Azure Zain,  He's A Gentleman
column36: Novice winner on last month's seasonal debut; can improve in handicaps but has tough draw
column37: Came second on all three 2yo starts and went one better in Kempton novice (7f, AW) on belated reappearance 16 days ago; should have some improvement to come in handicaps but his outside draw is a big negative.

column4: Virgin Bet Supports Safe Gambling Handicap
column20: 9/4 Mayday Malone, 13/2 Spirit Genie,  One More, 7/1 Documenting,  Benacre, 9/1 Zero Carbon, 10/1 Stratocracy, 14/1 Stanage, 20/1 Kindest Nation, 25/1 Maxi Boy,  Azure Zain,  He's A Gentleman
column36: Held on well to win Racing League event on AW last month and will be fine back on turf
column37: Front-runner who held on well to win Racing League event at Southwell (7f, AW) a fortnight ago; might have been better drawn here but will be fine back on turf and is probably still on a workable mark after 4lb rise.

column4: Virgin Bet Supports Safe Gambling Handicap
column20: 9/4 Mayday Malone, 13/2 Spirit Genie,  One More, 7/1 Documenting,  Benacre, 9/1 Zero Carbon, 10/1 Stratocracy, 14/1 Stanage, 20/1 Kindest Nation, 25/1 Maxi Boy,  Azure Zain,  He's A Gentleman
column36: Placed over 7.6f here in May but badly out of form since; headgear switched
column37: Now 11lb lower than when placed here (7.6f, good; visored) at the May meeting but has been badly out of form in the meantime; needs to be perked up by a change of headgear.

column4: Virgin Bet Supports Safe Gambling Handicap
column20: 9/4 Mayday Malone, 13/2 Spirit Genie,  One More, 7/1 Documenting,  Benacre, 9/1 Zero Carbon, 10/1 Stratocracy, 14/1 Stanage, 20/1 Kindest Nation, 25/1 Maxi Boy,  Azure Zain,  He's A Gentleman
column36: Very inconsistent in 2024 and not an easy one to predict on first start for ten months
column37: Came good for Fionn McSharry with clearcut 7f AW win in October but was very inconsistent last year and it's hard to know what to expect from him on this first start for ten months.

column4: Virgin Bet Supports Safe Gambling Handicap
column20: 9/4 Mayday Malone, 13/2 Spirit Genie,  One More, 7/1 Documenting,  Benacre, 9/1 Zero Carbon, 10/1 Stratocracy, 14/1 Stanage, 20/1 Kindest Nation, 25/1 Maxi Boy,  Azure Zain,  He's A Gentleman
column36: 1-6 as a sprinter; had excuses last time and this new trip may unlock improvement
column37: 6f AW novice winner in June; not much went to plan for him in major 6f turf handicap at Ripon last month but he's still unexposed after only six runs and today's step up in trip might unlock improvement.

column4: Virgin Bet Supports Safe Gambling Handicap
column20: 9/4 Mayday Malone, 13/2 Spirit Genie,  One More, 7/1 Documenting,  Benacre, 9/1 Zero Carbon, 10/1 Stratocracy, 14/1 Stanage, 20/1 Kindest Nation, 25/1 Maxi Boy,  Azure Zain,  He's A Gentleman
column36: Returned from break with poor run last month and has more to prove than some of these
column37: Has form on this track and was an AW winner in January but returned from break with a poor run last month and has more to prove than a few of these.

column4: Virgin Bet Supports Safe Gambling Handicap
column20: 9/4 Mayday Malone, 13/2 Spirit Genie,  One More, 7/1 Documenting,  Benacre, 9/1 Zero Carbon, 10/1 Stratocracy, 14/1 Stanage, 20/1 Kindest Nation, 25/1 Maxi Boy,  Azure Zain,  He's A Gentleman
column36: Did well to finish third here in July and is still in good form but has wide draw today
column37: Did well to finish third here (7.6f, good) in July, having taken a wide route into the straight, and has remained in good form since; might be aided by first-time visor today but wide draw makes things awkward.

column4: Virgin Bet Supports Safe Gambling Handicap
column20: 9/4 Mayday Malone, 13/2 Spirit Genie,  One More, 7/1 Documenting,  Benacre, 9/1 Zero Carbon, 10/1 Stratocracy, 14/1 Stanage, 20/1 Kindest Nation, 25/1 Maxi Boy,  Azure Zain,  He's A Gentleman
column32: Total Asbestos Solutions Ltd & A Frost
column36: Largely in good form this season but didn't fire last time and has double-digit draw here
column37: Began this season with five good efforts, the most notable a win at Newbury (7f, good to firm) in June, but was below form when last in action and has a double-digit draw here.

column4: Virgin Bet Supports Safe Gambling Handicap
column20: 9/4 Mayday Malone, 13/2 Spirit Genie,  One More, 7/1 Documenting,  Benacre, 9/1 Zero Carbon, 10/1 Stratocracy, 14/1 Stanage, 20/1 Kindest Nation, 25/1 Maxi Boy,  Azure Zain,  He's A Gentleman
column36: Five-time course winner who looked back in good nick when second at Haydock last month
column37: Five-time course winner (5f-7f); returned to form and ran a big race from the front when second at Haydock (7f, good) last month, and can be excused subsequent lesser effort (finished lame); respected back at Chester.

column4: Deepbridge Capital Fillies' Handicap
column20: 9/4 Vixey, 11/2 Autumn Rose, 6/1 Eazy On The Eye,  Little Keilee, 7/1 Musical Angel, 8/1 Lady Wingalong,  Bear Rock, 14/1 Hackney Diamonds
column36: As good as ever at Newbury two starts ago but probably needs to find even more here
column37: Looked as good as ever at Newbury (7f, good to firm) last month, holding on by a neck to make all, but was held off today's career-high mark 12 days later and probably needs to find hidden reserves here.

column4: Deepbridge Capital Fillies' Handicap
column20: 9/4 Vixey, 11/2 Autumn Rose, 6/1 Eazy On The Eye,  Little Keilee, 7/1 Musical Angel, 8/1 Lady Wingalong,  Bear Rock, 14/1 Hackney Diamonds
column36: Resurgent 5yo who posted career-best performance when strong-finishing second here in July
column37: Resurgent 5yo who has collected three wins this year and arguably posted career-best performance when strong-finishing second here (7.6f, good) in July, having been denied a clear run; commands respect.

column4: Deepbridge Capital Fillies' Handicap
column20: 9/4 Vixey, 11/2 Autumn Rose, 6/1 Eazy On The Eye,  Little Keilee, 7/1 Musical Angel, 8/1 Lady Wingalong,  Bear Rock, 14/1 Hackney Diamonds
column36: 6f maiden winner; moves up in trip after very respectable handicap run last month
column37: Displayed improvement to win 6f Brighton maiden in June (good to firm) and rebounded from disappointing handicap debut with very respectable third of five at Epsom (6f, good) last month; seemingly not one to rely upon heavily but could have untapped potential over 7f.

column4: Deepbridge Capital Fillies' Handicap
column20: 9/4 Vixey, 11/2 Autumn Rose, 6/1 Eazy On The Eye,  Little Keilee, 7/1 Musical Angel, 8/1 Lady Wingalong,  Bear Rock, 14/1 Hackney Diamonds
column36: Inconsistent in handicaps this year but the best form gives her good claims here
column37: Dual 8.6f AW winner in the autumn (maiden/novice); this year's handicap form is rather mixed but the highlights include a third at Sandown (1m, good to firm) and a front-running fifth of 16 at York (7f, good); can be very dangerous off current mark if on her mettle.

column4: Deepbridge Capital Fillies' Handicap
column20: 9/4 Vixey, 11/2 Autumn Rose, 6/1 Eazy On The Eye,  Little Keilee, 7/1 Musical Angel, 8/1 Lady Wingalong,  Bear Rock, 14/1 Hackney Diamonds
column36: Below form on latest outing but was in very good form over 6f in the spring and stays 7f
column37: Came good with narrow 6f win at Haydock in April and ran at least as well when very close second over that trip here (good) the following month; off since lesser effort ten weeks ago but stays 7f and enters calculations.

column4: Deepbridge Capital Fillies' Handicap
column20: 9/4 Vixey, 11/2 Autumn Rose, 6/1 Eazy On The Eye,  Little Keilee, 7/1 Musical Angel, 8/1 Lady Wingalong,  Bear Rock, 14/1 Hackney Diamonds
column36: Has posted some good efforts in defeat for new stable this season but comes with risk
column37: Ex-Irish 5yo who is 0-9 for James Owen since the spring; has posted some good efforts in defeat, most recently when third at Lingfield (7f, AW) last week, but her tendency to race too freely and/or start slowly is a nagging concern.

column4: Deepbridge Capital Fillies' Handicap

column20: 6/4 Suspended Sentence, 11/4 Magnatura, 100/30 Champion Island, 15/2 Assaranca, 10/1 Renovatio Angel
column32: G C Myddelton, C F E Hill & Partner
column36: Improved for 1m at Ripon last month and that form franked since; still capable of better
column37: Promise amidst inexperience on his first two starts and he still didn't look the finished article when leading on the line at Ripon four weeks ago on his first attempt at a mile; the runner-up has boosted that form since and he's a leading contender now handicapping.

column4: Anytime Fitness Nursery Handicap (GBBPlus Race)
column20: 6/4 Suspended Sentence, 11/4 Magnatura, 100/30 Champion Island, 15/2 Assaranca, 10/1 Renovatio Angel
column36: AW winner whose first 2 nursery starts were positive; less good latest; headgear now added
column37: Prominent racer; readily saw off his two rivals in a 7f novice at Chelmsford in June and his first two nursery runs were both solid efforts; well beaten at York three weeks ago and now moves up in distance with cheekpieces added.

column4: Anytime Fitness Nursery Handicap (GBBPlus Race)
column20: 6/4 Suspended Sentence, 11/4 Magnatura, 100/30 Champion Island, 15/2 Assaranca, 10/1 Renovatio Angel
column36: 7f nursery winner in July; stiff task latest; stamina for a mile has to be taken on trust
column37: Sprung a 16-1 surprise on his nursery debut at Leicester in July (7f, good to firm); two lesser efforts have followed but he faced a stiff task back at 6f at York's Ebor meeting three weeks ago; some encouragement for 1m on dam's side of pedigree but he's by a sprinter and it remains to be seen if he'll see it out, especially were the ground to deteriorate markedly.

column4: Anytime Fitness Nursery Handicap (GBBPlus Race)
column20: 6/4 Suspended Sentence, 11/4 Magnatura, 100/30 Champion Island, 15/2 Assaranca, 10/1 Renovatio Angel
column36: Improvement required to defy this mark but stepping up in trip could spark it
column37: No improvement for the switch to nurseries on her last two starts but she has run creditably on each occasion; needs to find more now upped to 1m for the first time (bred to stay).

column4: Molson Coors Beverage Company Handicap

column36: Needs to step up in his two efforts since returning to Europe; this is weaker, at least
column37: Two wins for the Gosdens, namely a 1m AW novice and a 7f handicap in Qatar; two runs since returning to Europe have been underwhelming though, albeit both have been tough assignments, and Native American may be the stable's main hope.

column4: Molson Coors Beverage Company Handicap
column20: 7/2 Billyjoh, 5/1 Native American,  Physique, 6/1 Crimson Spirit, 7/1 Blue For You, 8/1 Surrey Shadow, 10/1 Jayyash, 14/1 Crown Board,  Legal Reform, 20/1 Lexington Belle
column36: Best run for a while when 3rd at Epsom last month; today's more conventional track a plus
column37: Useful at two and three when trained by Richard Fahey; unable to win in the Middle East last winter but he ran his best race for a while when third of nine in a 7f handicap (good) at Epsom 18 days ago, plugging on having been outpaced in the straight; today's more conventional track should suit and he'll be fine on good to soft (unraced on slower).

column4: Molson Coors Beverage Company Handicap
column20: 7/2 Billyjoh, 5/1 Native American,  Physique, 6/1 Crimson Spirit, 7/1 Blue For You, 8/1 Surrey Shadow, 10/1 Jayyash, 14/1 Crown Board,  Legal Reform, 20/1 Lexington Belle
column36: Peak effort came at this track last September (1m, good); handicapper in command in 2025
column37: His easy win on his racecourse debut at Wolverhampton in December 2023 was foretold by the betting market; ran well in a Listed race (1m, good) here 12 months ago but he's enjoyed little success in handicaps this season; slowly edging down the weights but there are risks attached.

column4: Molson Coors Beverage Company Handicap
column20: 7/2 Billyjoh, 5/1 Native American,  Physique, 6/1 Crimson Spirit, 7/1 Blue For You, 8/1 Surrey Shadow, 10/1 Jayyash, 14/1 Crown Board,  Legal Reform, 20/1 Lexington Belle
column27: Cleartherm Glass Sealed Units & J Holt
column36: On a losing run but regularly goes well in strong handicaps; seems best on good or faster
column37: His losing run is building up a head of steam but he's usually seen contesting ultra-competitive handicaps and he regularly performs with credit; solid third in a Goodwood Class 2 three weeks ago (7f, good to firm); best form has come on good or faster turf so significant rain wouldn't be ideal.

column4: Molson Coors Beverage Company Handicap
column20: 7/2 Billyjoh, 5/1 Native American,  Physique, 6/1 Crimson Spirit, 7/1 Blue For You, 8/1 Surrey Shadow, 10/1 Jayyash, 14/1 Crown Board,  Legal Reform, 20/1 Lexington Belle
column36: Dropped to a dangerous mark and yard chasing hat-trick in this race; needs good pace at 7f
column37: His three wins in Britain have all come over 1m at York but he is fully effective at other tracks and he wasn't beaten far in his one Sandown run back in June 2022 (1m, good to firm); rain won't bother him and he's slipped to a dangerous mark but he will need a good pace to aim at back at 7f; stable have won the last two runnings.

column4: Molson Coors Beverage Company Handicap
column20: 7/2 Billyjoh, 5/1 Native American,  Physique, 6/1 Crimson Spirit, 7/1 Blue For You, 8/1 Surrey Shadow, 10/1 Jayyash, 14/1 Crown Board,  Legal Reform, 20/1 Lexington Belle
column36: 7f hat-trick in midsummer on good to firm (handles heavy); behind Native American latest
column37: Completed a 7f hat-trick this summer (all good to firm) and he wasn't beaten far off this mark at Musselburgh on his penultimate start; finished behind Native American when fourth at Epsom 18 days ago though and he'll need to deliver another career best; rain no concern.

column4: Molson Coors Beverage Company Handicap
column20: 7/2 Billyjoh, 5/1 Native American,  Physique, 6/1 Crimson Spirit, 7/1 Blue For You, 8/1 Surrey Shadow, 10/1 Jayyash, 14/1 Crown Board,  Legal Reform, 20/1 Lexington Belle
column36: In fine form on AW early in the year; last 2 runs need bettering and others look stronger
column37: In fine form on AW earlier in the year; below par returned to turf at Epsom in June and again at Southwell last month after 12 weeks off; all wins have come around a left-hand bend but he has gone desperately close at Musselburgh in the past; others perhaps better treated here.

column4: Molson Coors Beverage Company Handicap
column20: 7/2 Billyjoh, 5/1 Native American,  Physique, 6/1 Crimson Spirit, 7/1 Blue For You, 8/1 Surrey Shadow, 10/1 Jayyash, 14/1 Crown Board,  Legal Reform, 20/1 Lexington Belle
column36: In fine form last autumn on slow ground; 2025 efforts tepid; more rain to fall the better
column37: Came good 12 months ago when faced with testing ground so every drop of rain to fall beforehand will be welcomed; well beaten in two runs this year but quite possible she'll be seen to better effect this time.

column4: Molson Coors Beverage Company Handicap
column20: 7/2 Billyjoh, 5/1 Native American,  Physique, 6/1 Crimson Spirit, 7/1 Blue For You, 8/1 Surrey Shadow, 10/1 Jayyash, 14/1 Crown Board,  Legal Reform, 20/1 Lexington Belle
column36: 0-7 this year but he's often run well; tough draw latest; interesting on stable debut
column37: Failed to win in seven runs for Pam Sly this year but he often ran well; poor draw when down the field at Goodwood in July; can be competitive off this mark and won't mind how much rain there is; interesting starting out for a new stable (same owner) with the hood back on.

column4: Molson Coors Beverage Company Handicap
column20: 7/2 Billyjoh, 5/1 Native American,  Physique, 6/1 Crimson Spirit, 7/1 Blue For You, 8/1 Surrey Shadow, 10/1 Jayyash, 14/1 Crown Board,  Legal Reform, 20/1 Lexington Belle
column36: Fourth in the Spring Mile in March on just his fifth start; needs to settle better
column37: Hasn't kicked on as might have been expected from promising fourth of 21 in Spring Mile at Doncaster (good to soft) in March in two subsequent outings; still has time on his side though and he brings a different profile to most; needs to settle better but quite interesting.

column4: Rekorderlig Fillies' Handicap
column20: 100/30 Tropical Heat, 5/1 Sunlit Uplands, 11/2 Sea Poetry, 6/1 Dancing Colours, 8/1 Bint Mohaather, 10/1 Jakarta, 12/1 Mollie Foster,  Lady Mariko, 14/1 Ocean Treaty,  Purple Rainbow, 20/1 Brave Byreflection, 50/1 Miss Chester

column4: Rekorderlig Fillies' Handicap
column20: 100/30 Tropical Heat, 5/1 Sunlit Uplands, 11/2 Sea Poetry, 6/1 Dancing Colours, 8/1 Bint Mohaather, 10/1 Jakarta, 12/1 Mollie Foster,  Lady Mariko, 14/1 Ocean Treaty,  Purple Rainbow, 20/1 Brave Byreflection, 50/1 Miss Chester

column37: Four runs have yielded two wins and two seconds, showing her best form yet when upped to 7f at Haydock in May (good ground; handicap debut); had wind surgery in June; up 4lb but the Haydock form has worked out and she did well to extricate herself from a tricky spot; slow ground would be a unknown but she's thoroughly unexposed.

column4: Rekorderlig Fillies' Handicap
column20: 100/30 Tropical Heat, 5/1 Sunlit Uplands, 11/2 Sea Poetry, 6/1 Dancing Colours, 8/1 Bint Mohaather, 10/1 Jakarta, 12/1 Mollie Foster,  Lady Mariko, 14/1 Ocean Treaty,  Purple Rainbow, 20/1 Brave Byreflection, 50/1 Miss Chester

column4: Rekorderlig Fillies' Handicap

column4: Rekorderlig Fillies' Handicap

column37: Novice form was progressive, winning at Kempton (1m) in January before finishing fourth in a strong race at Ascot; yet to shine in handicaps, albeit latest York run (cheekpieces worn, absent today) was better, and the prospect of rain dims enthusiasm for a revival.

column4: Rekorderlig Fillies' Handicap

column37: Three runs in 7f fillies' novice events on AW have seen her run to a fair level, runner-up on last two; open to improvement now handicapping but it's likely she will need to raise her game.

column4: Rekorderlig Fillies' Handicap

column4: Rekorderlig Fillies' Handicap

column37: Confirmed the promise of her 2yo debut when running away with a 7f maiden at Wolverhampton in June; similar form when third at Doncaster in July but she didn't look ahead of the handicapper when third of five at Goodwood (1m, good) three weeks ago; return to 7f can help and not yet exposed.

column4: Rekorderlig Fillies' Handicap
column20: 100/30 Tropical Heat, 5/1 Sunlit Uplands, 11/2 Sea Poetry, 6/1 Dancing Colours, 8/1 Bint Mohaather, 10/1 Jakarta, 12/1 Mollie Foster,  Lady Mariko, 14/1 Ocean Treaty,  Purple Rainbow, 20/1 Brave Byreflection, 50/1 Miss Chester

column37: Improved for the step up to 7f, finishing second at Haydock in July before winning over C&D one week later; followed up at Haydock five weeks ago (overcame some adversity) and every chance there is more in the tank; 6lb rise demands it but slow ground might be more of a concern (unraced on slower than good).

column4: Rekorderlig Fillies' Handicap
column20: 100/30 Tropical Heat, 5/1 Sunlit Uplands, 11/2 Sea Poetry, 6/1 Dancing Colours, 8/1 Bint Mohaather, 10/1 Jakarta, 12/1 Mollie Foster,  Lady Mariko, 14/1 Ocean Treaty,  Purple Rainbow, 20/1 Brave Byreflection, 50/1 Miss Chester

column37: Won her first two starts for Dylan Cunha but came up short in her hat-trick bid at Newmarket last month; ran well in the face of a stiff task at York three weeks ago and these calmer waters will be more suitable; unraced on slower than good.

column4: Rekorderlig Fillies' Handicap

column37: Promise on debut (6f, AW) and put that experience to good use when making all over 7f on her second start; less good twice since, markedly so on her handicap debut (8.6f, Tapeta) last month; switches to turf with something to prove.

column37: Veteran who showed a fire still burned when winning a six-runner handicap at Lingfield (1m2f, good to soft) in June; third to Beach Point over C&D next time but his form has dipped on his last two starts; rain will help but vulnerable to less-exposed sorts.

column37: Sent off the 11-8 favourite when winning this race 12 months ago (soft); came into that race in better form but he's 2lb lower today and his latest run (behind a few of these) wasn't as bad as the distance beaten might suggest; the more rain the better for him.

column36: Three more wins this summer but looks vulnerable off this mark in Class 4 company

column37: C&D winner; yet to strike this season but he has run some fair races, notably his third of 12 at Windsor in May; returning to 1m2f is no problem and rain won't hurt (has won on soft); fully exposed but can't rule out off his reduced mark.
